The paper deals with facial micro-expression detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a recurrent neural network (RNN) for micro-expression spotting, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the application domains of lie detection, mental health, and sentiment analysis, which are related to human-computer interaction and fall under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also uses optical flow features, which are commonly used in multimedia analysis, falling under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Lastly, the paper discusses the annotation process, which is related to information retrieval and falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
